# Omninuera
Bengaluru (Headquarters)

Date: «[Offer Date]»

Offer of Internship – AI Intern

Dear [Candidate Name],

We are pleased to offer you an internship with Omninuera for the role of AI Intern on a stipend basis. Please find the key terms and conditions of the internship below. This is a draft offer for your review and acceptance. Please confirm your acceptance by signing and returning this letter.

1. Role and Employer
- Position: AI Intern.
- Employer: Omninuera (Bengaluru-headquartered and operating).
- Location: Completely remote (you will be located in Bengaluru and will work remotely).

2. Start Date and Duration
- Start Date: [Start Date]
- Duration: 3 months (the "Internship Period"), commencing on the Start Date unless otherwise agreed in writing.

3. Nature of Engagement; Employment Status
- This is an internship engagement on a stipend basis and does not create an employer-employee relationship.
- You will be an intern engaged with Omninuera for the Internship Period and, unless otherwise required by applicable law, you will not be entitled to statutory employment benefits (such as provident fund, gratuity, paid leave, etc.). If any statutory benefits are required by law to be provided despite the stipend nature, they will be applied as required.
- This Internship is not a guarantee of future employment with Omninuera.

4. Stipend and Payment Terms
- Stipend: INR 10,000 per month.
- Payment Schedule: Stipend will be paid monthly, on the last working Friday of each month through the company payroll (or the company’s standard payroll date), subject to any applicable deductions as required by law.
- Nature of Payment: This payment is a stipend for the Internship and not a salary or wage. It is intended to support expenses incurred by you during the Internship.
- Taxes: Omninuera may withhold taxes or other statutory deductions where required by law. You are responsible for your own personal tax compliance and reporting obligations arising from this stipend.

5. Working Hours and Commitment
- Expected commitment: Approximately 20 hours per week (or as mutually agreed). Working times may be flexible, subject to coordination with your Reporting Manager.
- Reporting Manager: [Reporting Manager Name].
- Deliverables and Reporting:
  - Weekly status updates to the Reporting Manager (format to be agreed).
  - Milestone-based deliverables as mutually agreed at the start of the Internship.
  - A final project deliverable or written report at the conclusion of the Internship, summarising work completed, outcomes and learnings.

6. Confidentiality and Intellectual Property
- Confidentiality: You will be required to keep confidential all non-public information of Omninuera and its clients or partners that you access during the Internship. You must not disclose, copy, or use such confidential information except as required for the performance of your duties. These obligations survive the termination of the Internship.
- IP Assignment: All inventions, discoveries, designs, developments, works of authorship, business methods, computer code, data, models, algorithms, improvements or other results that you create, develop or reduce to practice, individually or jointly, during the Internship and related to the business or activities of Omninuera (collectively, the "Internship IP") shall be the sole and exclusive property of Omninuera. You hereby irrevocably assign and transfer to Omninuera all right, title and interest in and to such Internship IP. You agree to execute such documents and provide such assistance as may be reasonably requested by Omninuera to secure, maintain and enforce its rights in the Internship IP.
- Confidentiality Agreement / NDA: As a condition of onboarding, you will be asked to sign Omninuera’s standard confidentiality agreement (or an equivalent NDA).

7. Termination
- Termination for convenience: Either party may terminate the Internship for any reason by giving seven (7) days' prior written notice to the other party.
- Termination for cause: Omninuera may terminate the Internship with immediate effect for cause, including but not limited to:
  - Material breach of this Offer or company policies (including code of conduct and data security policies);
  - Misconduct, dishonesty, fraud or actions that harm Omninuera or its clients;
  - Breach of confidentiality or unauthorised disclosure of company or client information;
  - Non-performance or failure to meet reasonable performance expectations after written notice.
- On termination, you must promptly return or destroy all company property and confidential materials in your possession, and any payments due will be processed in accordance with company policies and applicable law.

8. Conditions Precedent
- Background Verification: This offer is conditional upon successful completion of background verification checks (education, identity and other checks as applicable). Omninuera reserves the right to withdraw the offer if any discrepancy is found or if the checks are unsatisfactory.
- Eligibility: You must be a student or a recent graduate (as applicable) and must be eligible to undertake an internship under applicable law. You must promptly provide any documentation required to confirm your eligibility.
- Policies: You agree to comply with Omninuera’s policies, including but not limited to code of conduct, data security policy, privacy policy, remote work policy and any other applicable policies.

9. Remote Work Specifics
- Equipment and Workspace: You will generally be responsible for providing and maintaining your own equipment (computer, software, internet connectivity) and workspace unless Omninuera explicitly agrees in writing to provide equipment or reimburse expenses.
- Company-Provided Equipment: If Omninuera provides equipment, use will be governed by a separate agreement or equipment policy and you must return such equipment at the end of the Internship.
- Expenses and Reimbursements: Omninuera will reimburse pre-approved business expenses only if they are agreed in writing in advance and supported by appropriate receipts or evidence in line with Omninuera’s expense policy.
- Data Security and Tools: You must use company-approved tools and platforms for handling company data. You must follow Omninuera’s data security, password and access policies, and ensure confidentiality and secure handling of any company or client data.

10. Compliance with Laws and Policies
- You must comply with all applicable laws, rules and regulations while performing your duties.
- You must comply with Omninuera’s internal policies. Any violation of company policy may result in disciplinary action, including termination.

11. Reimbursement, Taxes and Deductions
- Reimbursements: Only pre-approved expenses with valid receipts will be reimbursed as per Omninuera’s policy.
- Tax Withholding: Omninuera may withhold amounts from stipend payments to comply with tax or other statutory obligations where required by law. You remain responsible for ensuring your tax filings and payments, where applicable.

12. Notices
- All notices under this Agreement shall be in writing and may be sent by email to the address you provide and to Omninuera’s designated email for such communications.

13. Governing Law
- This Offer shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of India. Disputes shall be subject to the appropriate courts having jurisdiction in Bengaluru, India.

14. Acceptance
If you agree to the terms of this Internship, please sign and date below and return a scanned copy of this signed letter to HR at [HR Email Address] by [Acceptance Deadline].

Candidate:
Signature: ______________________
Name: [Candidate Name]
Date: ______________________

For and on behalf of Omninuera:
Signature: ______________________
Name: [Authorized Representative Name]
Title: [Title]
Date: ______________________

Closing note
Please note that this is an internship offer and does not guarantee employment with Omninuera after completion of the Internship. Any offer of employment following the Internship will be subject to a separate agreement and may require additional approvals and checks.

---

Note to HR (Legal review requested)
Please forward this draft to Legal for careful review of the following clauses and issues:
- IP assignment: confirm clause is enforceable and appropriately scoped for student/intern-created work.
- Stipend vs. wage classification: confirm stipend wording and ensure compliance with labour laws and any minimum wage/statutory requirements that may apply to interns in India.
- Labour/statutory compliance: confirm whether any statutory benefits (PF, ESI, gratuity, etc.) apply to this stipend-based internship under Indian law and local Bengaluru rules.
- Data protection and cross-border data transfer: review data security clauses, any processing of personal data and whether cross-border transfers are involved requiring additional safeguards.
- Remote-work liabilities: review liability allocation for work-from-home incidents, workplace ergonomics, and health & safety obligations (if any).
- Background verification legality: confirm scope and permissible checks under Indian law and consent wording.
- Tax withholding: confirm employer withholding obligations for stipends and any reporting requirements.
- Any mandatory policies or disclosures required for student interns under applicable Bengaluru/India rules.

Please advise any required wording changes. Once Legal provides comments, HR will update the draft accordingly and produce a final offer letter for signature.
